cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

This paper proposes a novel fully convolutional network (FCN) framework for salient object detection that integrates multilevel convolutional features recurrently with the guidance of object boundary information. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically salient object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely arXiv CS sub-category. The paper also utilizes deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed framework involves attention-based feature fusion, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, and thus, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates its proposed framework on four large-scale benchmarks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
